# SRT Chapter Splitter — Implementation Plan

Ứng dụng PyQt6 Desktop để chia file SRT kịch bản YouTube thành các chapter lớn bằng AI. Hỗ trợ 2 loại kịch bản: dạng Top/List (mỗi chapter độc lập) và dạng liền mạch (chia theo luận điểm/mạch kể). Xử lý batch, xác minh tự động, lưu kết quả từng item ngay khi hoàn thành.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Structure

```
2.Script_Split_Chapter/
├── main.py                    # Entry point
├── requirements.txt           # PyQt6, requests
├── core/                      # Backend logic (no UI imports)
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── api_client.py          # Multi-endpoint API router + failover
│   ├── config_manager.py      # JSON config save/load per-tab
│   ├── srt_parser.py          # Parse .srt files
│   ├── chapter_splitter.py    # AI chapter splitting + verification
│   └── process_controller.py  # ThreadPoolExecutor, start/pause/stop
├── ui/                        # All UI components
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── theme.py               # Dark/Light QSS + apply_theme()
│   ├── icons/                 # SVG arrows for ComboBox/SpinBox
│   │   ├── arrow_down.svg
│   │   └── arrow_up.svg
│   ├── searchable_combo.py    # QComboBox with filter popup
│   ├── log_section.py         # Processing Log panel (copy, clear)
│   ├── header_bar.py          # App name, version, Settings, Restart
│   ├── settings_dialog.py     # Endpoints, Theme, API keys
│   ├── projects_section.py    # QTreeWidget with folder grouping
│   ├── chapter_tab.py         # Main tab: config + projects + actions
│   └── main_window.py         # QMainWindow + QTabWidget + splitter
├── prompts/                   # External .txt prompt files
│   ├── system_toplist.txt     # System prompt for Top/List scripts
│   ├── system_narrative.txt   # System prompt for Narrative scripts
│   ├── system_verify.txt      # Verification prompt
│   └── fallback_chapter.txt   # Default fallback
├── logs/                      # API call history (auto-created)
└── output/                    # Generated chapter files (auto-created)
```

---

### Core Backend

#### [NEW] [api_client.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py)
- Class `APIClient` — multi-endpoint router
- Loads endpoints from `api_keys.json` (base_url, api_key, model, enabled)
- `call_api(messages, endpoint_index)` — sends request, returns response
- Auto-failover: on HTTP 429/5xx, tries next enabled endpoint
- Optional API logging to `logs/api_history.jsonl` (timestamp, endpoint, model, prompt, response, status_code)

#### [NEW] [config_manager.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/config_manager.py)
- `save_config(tab_name, data)` → saves to `{tab_name}_config.json`
- `load_config(tab_name)` → loads from JSON, returns dict
- `save_api_keys(endpoints)` / `load_api_keys()` → `api_keys.json`
- `save_settings(settings)` / `load_settings()` → `settings.json` (theme, language)

#### [NEW] [srt_parser.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/srt_parser.py)
- `parse_srt(filepath)` → returns list of `SrtEntry(index, start, end, text)`
- `srt_to_text(entries, include_timecodes)` → plain text optionally with timecodes
- Handles UTF-8 BOM, various line endings

#### [NEW] [chapter_splitter.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/chapter_splitter.py)
- `split_chapters(srt_text, script_type, api_client, include_timestamps)` → list of Chapter objects
- Two modes: `top_list` (independent entities) and `narrative` (analyze structure)
- Reads prompts from `prompts/system_toplist.txt` or `prompts/system_narrative.txt`
- Verification step: calls AI again with `prompts/system_verify.txt` to validate chapters
- `save_chapters(chapters, output_dir, base_filename)` → saves each chapter as separate .txt
- `merge_chapters(chapters, output_dir, base_filename)` → single merged .txt
- `save_summary(chapters, output_dir, base_filename)` → summary .txt file
- **Preserves original SRT content 100%** — no text modification

#### [NEW] [process_controller.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/process_controller.py)
- `ProcessController` with `ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=threads)`
- State machine: IDLE → RUNNING ↔ PAUSED → STOPPED → IDLE
- `start(items, callback)`, `pause()`, `resume()`, `stop()`
- Uses `threading.Event` for pause/resume
- Auto-save: saves result immediately when each item completes
- Emits progress via callback (thread-safe, UI updates via `QTimer.singleShot`)

